The ANC’s secretariat has sent condolences to the families of the first two South Africans to die of the novel coronavirus. On Friday, Health Minister Zweli Mkhize announced that two women from the Western Cape had died of the coronavirus, as the number of positive cases shot past 1 000. The ANC’s secretary-general, Ace Magashule, said the party remained confident the measures announced by President Cyril Ramaphosa, and the guidelines set out by the health department, would contribute to the country overcoming the virus. Measures “The latest measures are indicative of the level of seriousness by government to ensure that the devastating effects of the virus are contained,” said Magashule in a statement. He also called on authorities to strictly enforce the measures set out by the president. Magashule commended the health workers who were at the “coalface” of the country’s battle against the coronavirus. “We also extend our appreciation to the security forces for responding enthusiastically to the call from President Cyril Ramaphosa to lend a hand in this national effort to defeat the pandemic,” said Magashule. Magashule's deputy, Jessie Duarte, sent out messages of support to the families of the two women who died, and called on South Africans to follow the rules in order to stay safe and healthy. https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/coronavirus-ace-durte-send-condolences-to-families-of-2-dead-20200327